1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
A green build is not a shippable game. PlayReceipt turns reliability, balance, accessibility, and human-play evidence into a stable release receipt.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:47,000
The real read-only snapshot ran 2,000 seeded simulations without crashes or stalls, but weak strategy separation, missing reduced motion, and no human fun calibration keep the verdict at REPAIR.

3
00:00:47,000 --> 00:01:07,000
The repaired sandbox passes seven machine-verifiable gates with no missing inputs. PlayReceipt still stops at HUMAN REVIEW because simulation cannot certify fun.

4
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:27,000
Identical evidence produces an identical SHA-256 receipt. Meaningful CLI exit codes, seven regression tests, and a repository-local Codex skill make the decision reproducible.

5
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:41,000
PlayReceipt is new OpenAI Build Week work. Try the live deployment and inspect every claim in the public repository.
